Afropop sensation, Mark Owoicho aka Mark Owi has taken over the entirety of Benue in an unprecedented style. After shutting down Benue and Calabar with several performances in December 2021, the winner of ‘Idoma Got Talent’ has continued to wow music enthusiasts. Owi made news after signing a record deal with Osas vision music (OVM), a UK-based Record Label, recently.   Miracle Nduka breaks new grounds     The Queen of Flow returns for Season 2     SiSobola promises to always put smiles on people’s faces   According to those in the know, Owi seems to have monopolised the music scene in the middle belt areas as fans couldn’t stop shouting his name while performing at the Ochacho Music Carnival, held in Otukpo Benue State. The Carnival which played host to superstars like D’banj, 2face, Ladipoe, black Face, Faze alone and other prominent individuals/stars further cemented Owi’s singing prowess. He also graced and performed at one of the most prominent shows in the whole of Benue State – Made In Benue (All White Party) held in Makurdi. Mark also paid a courtesy visit to the Executive Governor of Benue State, His Excellency Samuel Ortom, who received him and other superstars in the entertainment industry.